HEADWORD: Manes
<hw>Ma"nes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>The benevolent spirits of the dead,
especially of dead ancestors, regarded as family deities and
protectors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hail, O ye holy <qex>manes</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

